column4: Describe a positive memory involving one or more members of the class of 2021. What impact did this have on you?

Tomer sedan was my mentor going through highschool he taught me everything i know and is super cool as well 😁. Additionally martin chaperot was also a great help and they are just cool dudes. But if i had to name another cool person it would be guy Ben zehez he taught to climb and has a really cool jacket.
Jack Burns has been one of the best things that has happened to me during my freshman year. He’s always so kind and considerate and I'm glad that I'm his friend.
